transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, I've been getting a prescription sent through the mail every few months and I want

Speaker 2: to cancel that, please.

Speaker 1: All right, let me pull up your account, sir.

Speaker 2: And is your name Jonathan?

Speaker 1: Yes, Jonathan Clark.

Speaker 2: All right, one moment.

Speaker 1: All right, sir, so I do see your VIP customer getting a Viagra from us.

Speaker 2: Do you mind if I ask why it is you're canceling today?

Speaker 1: Several reasons and I don't have time to go into it.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: That is a lot of reasons.

Speaker 2: It is a lot of reasons, yes.

Speaker 1: Well, there's one thing I can do for you.

Speaker 2: You know you can order this stuff as needed, right?

Speaker 1: You do not have to get this automatically or when you're not ready.

Speaker 2: Would it be easier to kind of just order as needed?

Speaker 1: Okay, you could change it to that.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that would be fine.

Speaker 1: I'm sorry, sir, what did you say?

Speaker 2: Sorry?

Speaker 1: I didn't hear what you said, sir.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry.

Speaker 1: Let's just go ahead and cancel it.

Speaker 2: Okay, so you don't want to order as needed?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: All right, we'll take care of it for you, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.
